The paper deals with a data structure for answering range majority queries on a dynamic set of points, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and databases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and deals with heavy hitters, which are common topics in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also mentions d-dimensional points, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
